{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["41-MRK-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "MRK"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Marqus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Good News According to Marqus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Marqus \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Mrk \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Good News According to \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Marqus \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 1:1"}, "The beginning of the Good News of Al Masih Isa, the Son of Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 1:2"}, "As it is written in the prophets, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u1f30\u03b4\u03bf\u1f7a\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often used as\nan interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " I send my messenger before your face, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who will prepare your way before you:", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Malachi\n3:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 1:3"}, "the voice of one crying in the wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018Make ready the way of the Lord! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Make his paths straight!\u2019\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["1:3 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 40:3"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 1:4"}, "Yahya came baptising", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, immersing"]}], "caller": "+"}, " in the wilderness and preaching the baptism of repentance for\nforgiveness of sins. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 1:5"}, "All the country of Judea and all those of Jerusalem went out to him. They were baptised by him in the Jordan river,\nconfessing their sins. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 1:6"}, "Yahya was clothed with camel\u2019s hair and a leather belt around his waist. He ate locusts and wild honey.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 1:7"}, "He preached, saying, \u201cAfter me comes he who is mightier than I, the thong of whose sandals I am not worthy to stoop down\nand loosen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 1:8"}, "I baptised you in", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Greek word (en) translated here as \u201cin\u201d could also be translated as \u201cwith\u201d in some\ncontexts."]}], "caller": "+"}, " water, but he will baptise you in the Holy Spirit.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 1:9"}, "In those days, Isa came from Nazareth of Galilee, and was baptised by Yahya in the Jordan.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 1:10"}, "Immediately coming up from the water, he saw the heavens parting, and the Spirit descending on him like a dove.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 1:11"}, "A voice came out of the sky, \u201cYou are my beloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 1:12"}, "Immediately the Spirit drove him out into the wilderness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 1:13"}, "He was there in the wilderness forty days tempted by Iblis. He was with the wild animals; and the angels were serving\nhim. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 1:14"}, "Now after Yahya was taken into custody, Isa came into Galilee, preaching the Good News of Allah\u2019s Kingdom,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 1:15"}, "and saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe time is fulfilled, and Allah\u2019s Kingdom is at hand! Repent, and believe in the Good\nNews.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 1:16"}, "Passing along by the sea of Galilee, he saw Shima\u2019un and Andreas, the brother of Shima\u2019un, casting a net into the sea,\nfor they were fishermen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 1:17"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCome after me, and I will make you into fishers for\nmen.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 1:18"}, "Immediately they left their nets, and followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 1:19"}, "Going on a little further from there, he saw Yaqub the son of Zebedee, and Yuhanna, his brother, who were also in the\nboat mending the nets. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 1:20"}, "Immediately he called them, and they left their father, Zebedee, in the boat with the hired servants, and went after him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 1:21"}, "They went into Capernaum, and immediately on the Sabbath day he entered into the synagogue and taught.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 1:22"}, "They were astonished at his teaching, for he taught them as having authority, and not as the scribes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 1:23"}, "Immediately there was in their synagogue a man with an unclean spirit, and he cried out,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 1:24"}, "saying, \u201cHa! What do we have to do with you, Isa, you Nazarene? Have you come to destroy us? I know you who you are: the\nHoly One of Allah!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 1:25"}, "Isa rebuked him, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBe quiet, and come out of him!\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 1:26"}, "The unclean spirit, convulsing him and crying with a loud voice, came out of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 1:27"}, "They were all amazed, so that they questioned amongst themselves, saying, \u201cWhat is this? A new teaching? For with\nauthority he commands even the unclean spirits, and they obey him!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 1:28"}, "The report of him went out immediately everywhere into all the region of Galilee and its surrounding area.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 1:29"}, "Immediately, when they had come out of the synagogue, they came into the house of Shima\u2019un and Andreas, with Yaqub and\nYuhanna. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 1:30"}, "Now Shima\u2019un\u2019s wife\u2019s mother lay sick with a fever, and immediately they told him about her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 1:31"}, "He came and took her by the hand, and raised her up. The fever left her\nimmediately,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:31"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits \u201cimmediately\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and she served them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 1:32"}, "At evening, when the sun had set, they brought to him all who were sick, and those who were possessed by demons.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 1:33"}, "All the city was gathered together at the door. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 1:34"}, "He healed many who were sick with various diseases, and cast out many demons. He didn\u2019t allow the demons to speak,\nbecause they knew him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 1:35"}, "Early in the morning, while it was still dark, he rose up and went out, and departed into a deserted place, and prayed\nthere. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 1:36"}, "Shima\u2019un and those who were with him searched for him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 1:37"}, "They found him and told him, \u201cEveryone is looking for you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 1:38"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cLet\u2019s go elsewhere into the next towns, that I may preach there also, because I came out for this\nreason.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 1:39"}, "He went into their synagogues throughout all Galilee, preaching and casting out demons.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 1:40"}, "A leper came to him, begging him, kneeling down to him, and saying to him, \u201cIf you want to, you can make me clean.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 1:41"}, "Being moved with compassion, he stretched out his hand, and touched him, and said to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI want to. Be made clean.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 1:42"}, "When he had said this, immediately the leprosy departed from him, and he was made clean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 1:43"}, "He strictly warned him, and immediately sent him out, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 1:44"}, "and said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSee you say nothing to anybody, but go show yourself to the priest, and offer for your cleansing\nthe things which Musa commanded, for a testimony to them.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 1:45"}, "But he went out, and began to proclaim it much, and to spread about the matter, so that Isa could no more openly enter\ninto a city, but was outside in desert places. People came to him from everywhere.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 2:1"}, "When he entered again into Capernaum after some days, it was heard that he was in the house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 2:2"}, "Immediately many were gathered together, so that there was no more room, not even around the door; and he spoke the word\nto them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 2:3"}, "Four people came, carrying a paralytic to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 2:4"}, "When they could not come near to him for the crowd, they removed the roof where he was. When they had broken it up, they\nlet down the mat that the paralytic was lying on. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 2:5"}, "Isa, seeing their faith, said to the paralytic, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSon, your sins are forgiven\nyou.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 2:6"}, "But there were some of the scribes sitting there, and reasoning in their hearts,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 2:7"}, "\u201cWhy does this man speak blasphemies like that? Who can forgive sins but Allah alone?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 2:8"}, "Immediately Isa, perceiving in his spirit that they so reasoned within themselves, said to them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you reason these things in your hearts? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 2:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Which is easier, to tell the paralytic, \u2018Your sins are forgiven;\u2019 or to say, \u2018Arise, and take up your bed, and walk?\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 2:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But that you may know that the Son of Man has authority on earth to forgive\nsins\u201d"]}, "\u2014he said to the paralytic\u2014 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 2:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI tell you, arise, take up your mat, and go to your house.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 2:12"}, "He arose, and immediately took up the mat, and went out in front of them all; so that they were all amazed, and glorified\nAllah, saying, \u201cWe never saw anything like this!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 2:13"}, "He went out again by the seaside. All the multitude came to him, and he taught them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 2:14"}, "As he passed by, he saw Levi, the son of Alphaeus, sitting at the tax office, and he said to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFollow me.\u201d"]}, " And he arose and followed him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 2:15"}, "He was reclining at the table in his house, and many tax collectors and sinners sat down with Isa and his disciples, for\nthere were many, and they followed him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 2:16"}, "The scribes and the Pharisees, when they saw that he was eating with the sinners and tax collectors, said to his\ndisciples, \u201cWhy is it that he eats and drinks with tax collectors and sinners?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 2:17"}, "When Isa heard it, he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThose who are healthy have no need for a physician, but those who are sick. I\ncame not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 2:18"}, "Yahya\u2019s disciples and the Pharisees were fasting, and they came and asked him, \u201cWhy do Yahya\u2019s disciples and the\ndisciples of the Pharisees fast, but your disciples don\u2019t fast?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 2:19"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCan the groomsmen fast while the bridegroom is with them? As long as they have the bridegroom with\nthem, they can\u2019t fast. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 2:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But the days will come when the bridegroom will be taken away from them, and then they will fast in that day.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 2:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["No one sews a piece of unshrunk cloth on an old garment, or else the patch shrinks and the new tears away from the\nold, and a worse hole is made. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 2:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["No one puts new wine into old wineskins, or else the new wine will burst the skins, and the wine pours out, and the\nskins will be destroyed; but they put new wine into fresh wineskins.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 2:23"}, "He was going on the Sabbath day through the grain fields, and his disciples began, as they went, to pluck the ears of\ngrain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 2:24"}, "The Pharisees said to him, \u201cBehold, why do they do that which is not lawful on the Sabbath day?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 2:25"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDid you never read what Dawood did, when he had need, and was hungry\u2014he, and those who were with\nhim? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 2:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["How he entered into Allah\u2019s house at the time of Abiathar the high priest, and ate the show bread, which is not\nlawful to eat except for the priests, and gave also to those who were with\nhim?\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 2:27"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Sabbath was made for man, not man for the Sabbath.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 2:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore the Son of Man is lord even of the Sabbath.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 3:1"}, "He entered again into the synagogue, and there was a man there who had his hand withered.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 3:2"}, "They watched him, whether he would heal him on the Sabbath day, that they might accuse him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 3:3"}, "He said to the man who had his hand withered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cStand up.\u201d"]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 3:4"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIs it lawful on the Sabbath day to do good, or to do harm? To save a life, or to\nkill?\u201d"]}, " But they were silent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 3:5"}, "When he had looked around at them with anger, being grieved at the hardening of their hearts, he said to the man,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cStretch out your hand.\u201d "]}, " He stretched it out, and his hand was restored as healthy as the other.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 3:6"}, "The Pharisees went out, and immediately conspired with the Herodians against him, how they might destroy him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 3:7"}, "Isa withdrew to the sea with his disciples, and a great multitude followed him from Galilee, from Judea,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 3:8"}, "from Jerusalem, from Idumaea, beyond the Jordan, and those from around Tyre and Sidon. A great multitude, hearing what\ngreat things he did, came to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 3:9"}, "He spoke to his disciples that a little boat should stay near him because of the crowd, so that they wouldn\u2019t press on\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 3:10"}, "For he had healed many, so that as many as had diseases pressed on him that they might touch him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 3:11"}, "The unclean spirits, whenever they saw him, fell down before him, and cried, \u201cYou are the Son of Allah!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 3:12"}, "He sternly warned them that they should not make him known.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 3:13"}, "He went up into the mountain, and called to himself those whom he wanted, and they went to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 3:14"}, "He appointed twelve, that they might be with him, and that he might send them out to preach,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 3:15"}, "and to have authority to heal sicknesses and to cast out demons:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 3:16"}, "Shima\u2019un (to whom he gave the name Peter); \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 3:17"}, "Yaqub the son of Zebedee; and Yuhanna, the brother of Yaqub, (whom he called Boanerges, which means, Sons of Thunder);\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 3:18"}, "Andreas; Philip; Bar-Talmai; Matti; Tau\u2019ma; Yaqub, the son of Alphaeus; Theudas; Shima\u2019un the Zealot;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 3:19"}, "and Yehuda Iscariot, who also betrayed him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then he came into a house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 3:20"}, "The multitude came together again, so that they could not so much as eat bread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 3:21"}, "When his friends heard it, they went out to seize him; for they said, \u201cHe is insane.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 3:22"}, "The scribes who came down from Jerusalem said, \u201cHe has Beelzebul,\u201d and, \u201cBy the prince of the demons he casts out the\ndemons.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 3:23"}, "He summoned them, and said to them in parables, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow can Iblis cast out Satan?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 3:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If a kingdom is divided against itself, that kingdom cannot stand.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 3:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If a house is divided against itself, that house cannot stand.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 3:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If Iblis has risen up against himself, and is divided, he can\u2019t stand, but has an end.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 3:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But no one can enter into the house of the strong man to plunder unless he first binds the strong man; then he will\nplunder his house. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 3:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, all sins of the descendants of man will be forgiven, including their blasphemies with\nwhich they may blaspheme; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 3:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but whoever may blaspheme against the Holy Spirit never has forgiveness, but is subject to eternal\ncondemnation.\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:29 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU reads, guilty of an eternal\nsin."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 3:30"}, "\u2014because they said, \u201cHe has an unclean spirit.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 3:31"}, "His mother and his brothers came, and standing outside, they sent to him, calling him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 3:32"}, "A multitude was sitting around him, and they told him, \u201cBehold, your mother, your brothers, and your\nsisters", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201cyour sisters\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " are outside looking for you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 3:33"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho are my mother and my brothers?\u201d"]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 3:34"}, "Looking around at those who sat around him, he said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, my mother and my brothers!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 3:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever does the will of Allah is my brother, my sister, and\nmother.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 4:1"}, "Again he began to teach by the seaside. A great multitude was gathered to him, so that he entered into a boat in the sea,\nand sat down. All the multitude were on the land by the sea. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 4:2"}, "He taught them many things in parables, and told them in his teaching,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 4:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cListen! Behold, the farmer went out to sow, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 4:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and as he sowed, some seed fell by the road, and the birds"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cof the air\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["came and devoured it. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 4:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell on the rocky ground, where it had little soil, and immediately it sprang up, because it had no depth of\nsoil. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 4:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When the sun had risen, it was scorched; and because it had no root, it withered away.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 4:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell amongst the thorns, and the thorns grew up, and choked it, and it yielded no fruit.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 4:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others fell into the good ground, and yielded fruit, growing up and increasing. Some produced thirty times, some\nsixty times, and some one hundred times as much.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 4:9"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhoever has ears to hear, let him hear.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 4:10"}, "When he was alone, those who were around him with the twelve asked him about the parables.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 4:11"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTo you is given the mystery of Allah\u2019s Kingdom, but to those who are outside, all things are done\nin parables, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 4:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["that \u2018seeing they may see, and not perceive; and hearing they may hear, and not understand; lest perhaps they should\nturn again, and their sins should be forgiven them.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["4:12\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 6:9-10"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 4:13"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t you understand this parable? How will you understand all of the parables?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 4:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The farmer sows the word. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 4:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The ones by the road are the ones where the word is sown; and when they have heard, immediately Iblis comes, and\ntakes away the word which has been sown in them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 4:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["These in the same way are those who are sown on the rocky places, who, when they have heard the word, immediately\nreceive it with joy. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 4:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["They have no root in themselves, but are short-lived. When oppression or persecution arises because of the word,\nimmediately they stumble. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 4:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Others are those who are sown amongst the thorns. These are those who have heard the word,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 4:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and the cares of this age, and the deceitfulness of riches, and the lusts of other things entering in choke the\nword, and it becomes unfruitful. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 4:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Those which were sown on the good ground are those who hear the word, and accept it, and bear fruit, some thirty\ntimes, some sixty times, and some one hundred times.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 4:21"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIs the lamp brought to be put under a basket\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["4:21 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, a modion, a dry measuring basket containing about a peck (about 9\nlitres)"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["or under a bed? Isn\u2019t it put on a stand? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 4:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For there is nothing hidden, except that it should be made known; neither was anything made secret, but that it\nshould come to light. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 4:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If any man has ears to hear, let him hear.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 4:24"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake heed what you hear. With whatever measure you measure, it will be measured to you, and more\nwill be given to you who hear. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 4:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever has, to him more will be given, and he who doesn\u2019t have, even that which he has will be taken away from\nhim.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 4:26"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAllah\u2019s Kingdom is as if a man should cast seed on the earth,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 4:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and should sleep and rise night and day, and the seed should spring up and grow, though he doesn\u2019t know how.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 4:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the earth bears fruit: first the blade, then the ear, then the full grain in the ear.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 4:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when the fruit is ripe, immediately he puts in the sickle, because the harvest has\ncome.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 4:30"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow will we liken Allah\u2019s Kingdom? Or with what parable will we illustrate it?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 4:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It\u2019s like a grain of mustard seed, which, when it is sown in the earth, though it is less than all the seeds that\nare on the earth, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 4:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["yet when it is sown, grows up, and becomes greater than all the herbs, and puts out great branches, so that the\nbirds of the sky can lodge under its shadow.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 4:33"}, "With many such parables he spoke the word to them, as they were able to hear it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 4:34"}, "Without a parable he didn\u2019t speak to them; but privately to his own disciples he explained everything.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 4:35"}, "On that day, when evening had come, he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cLet\u2019s go over to the other\nside.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 4:36"}, "Leaving the multitude, they took him with them, even as he was, in the boat. Other small boats were also with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 4:37"}, "A big wind storm arose, and the waves beat into the boat, so much that the boat was already filled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 4:38"}, "He himself was in the stern, asleep on the cushion, and they woke him up, and told him, \u201cTeacher, don\u2019t you care that we\nare dying?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 4:39"}, "He awoke, and rebuked the wind, and said to the sea, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cPeace! Be\nstill!\u201d"]}, " The wind ceased, and there was a great calm. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 4:40"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy are you so afraid? How is it that you have no\nfaith?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 4:41"}, "They were greatly afraid, and said to one another, \u201cWho then is this, that even the wind and the sea obey him?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 5:1"}, "They came to the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 5:2"}, "When he had come out of the boat, immediately a man with an unclean spirit met him out of the tombs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 5:3"}, "He lived in the tombs. Nobody could bind him any more, not even with chains,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 5:4"}, "because he had been often bound with fetters and chains, and the chains had been torn apart by him, and the fetters broken\nin pieces. Nobody had the strength to tame him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 5:5"}, "Always, night and day, in the tombs and in the mountains, he was crying out, and cutting himself with stones.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 5:6"}, "When he saw Isa from afar, he ran and bowed down to him, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 5:7"}, "and crying out with a loud voice, he said, \u201cWhat have I to do with you, Isa, you Son of the Most High Allah? I adjure you\nby Allah, don\u2019t torment me.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 5:8"}, "For he said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCome out of the man, you unclean spirit!\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 5:9"}, "He asked him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat is your name?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to him, \u201cMy name is Legion, for we are many.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 5:10"}, "He begged him much that he would not send them away out of the country.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 5:11"}, "Now on the mountainside there was a great herd of pigs feeding.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 5:12"}, "All the demons begged him, saying, \u201cSend us into the pigs, that we may enter into them.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 5:13"}, "At once Isa gave them permission. The unclean spirits came out and entered into the pigs. The herd of about two thousand\nrushed down the steep bank into the sea, and they were drowned in the sea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 5:14"}, "Those who fed them fled, and told it in the city and in the country.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The people came to see what it was that had happened. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 5:15"}, "They came to Isa, and saw him who had been possessed by demons sitting, clothed, and in his right mind, even him who had\nthe legion; and they were afraid. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 5:16"}, "Those who saw it declared to them what happened to him who was possessed by demons, and about the pigs.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 5:17"}, "They began to beg him to depart from their region. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 5:18"}, "As he was entering into the boat, he who had been possessed by demons begged him that he might be with him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 5:19"}, "He didn\u2019t allow him, but said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo to your house, to your friends, and tell them what great things the Lord\nhas done for you, and how he had mercy on you.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 5:20"}, "He went his way, and began to proclaim in Decapolis how Isa had done great things for him, and everyone marvelled.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 5:21"}, "When Isa had crossed back over in the boat to the other side, a great multitude was gathered to him; and he was by the\nsea. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 5:22"}, "Behold, one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jairus by name, came; and seeing him, he fell at his feet,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 5:23"}, "and begged him much, saying, \u201cMy little daughter is at the point of death. Please come and lay your hands on her, that\nshe may be made healthy, and live.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 5:24"}, "He went with him, and a great multitude followed him, and they pressed upon him on all sides.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 5:25"}, "A certain woman, who had a discharge of blood for twelve years,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 5:26"}, "and had suffered many things by many physicians, and had spent all that she had, and was no better, but rather grew\nworse, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 5:27"}, "having heard the things concerning Isa, came up behind him in the crowd, and touched his clothes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 5:28"}, "For she said, \u201cIf I just touch his clothes, I will be made well.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 5:29"}, "Immediately the flow of her blood was dried up, and she felt in her body that she was healed of her affliction.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 5:30"}, "Immediately Isa, perceiving in himself that the power had gone out from him, turned around in the crowd, and asked,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho touched my clothes?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 5:31"}, "His disciples said to him, \u201cYou see the multitude pressing against you, and you say, \u2018Who touched me?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 5:32"}, "He looked around to see her who had done this thing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 5:33"}, "But the woman, fearing and trembling, knowing what had been done to her, came and fell down before him, and told him all\nthe truth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 5:34"}, "He said to her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDaughter, your faith has made you well. Go in peace, and be cured of your\ndisease.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 5:35"}, "While he was still speaking, people came from the synagogue ruler\u2019s house saying, \u201cYour daughter is dead. Why bother the\nTeacher any more?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 5:36"}, "But Isa, when he heard the message spoken, immediately said to the ruler of the synagogue,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, only believe.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 5:37"}, "He allowed no one to follow him, except Peter, Yaqub, and Yuhanna the brother of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 5:38"}, "He came to the synagogue ruler\u2019s house, and he saw an uproar, weeping, and great wailing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 5:39"}, "When he had entered in, he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you make an uproar and weep? The child is not dead, but is\nasleep.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 5:40"}, "They ridiculed him. But he, having put them all out, took the father of the child, her mother, and those who were with\nhim, and went in where the child was lying. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 5:41"}, "Taking the child by the hand, he said to her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTalitha cumi!\u201d\n"]}, " which means, being interpreted, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGirl, I tell you, get up!\u201d\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 5:42"}, "Immediately the girl rose up and walked, for she was twelve years old. They were amazed with great amazement.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 5:43"}, "He strictly ordered them that no one should know this, and commanded that something should be given to her to eat.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 6:1"}, "He went out from there. He came into his own country, and his disciples followed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 6:2"}, "When the Sabbath had come, he began to teach in the synagogue, and many hearing him were astonished, saying, \u201cWhere did\nthis man get these things?\u201d and, \u201cWhat is the wisdom that is given to this man, that such mighty works come about by his hands?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 6:3"}, "Isn\u2019t this the carpenter, the son of Maryam, and brother of Yaqub, Joses, Judah, and Shima\u2019un? Aren\u2019t his sisters here\nwith us?\u201d They were offended at him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 6:4"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cA prophet is not without honour, except in his own country, and amongst his own relatives, and in\nhis own house.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 6:5"}, "He could do no mighty work there, except that he laid his hands on a few sick people, and healed them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 6:6"}, "He marvelled because of their unbelief. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He went around the villages teaching. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 6:7"}, "He called to himself the twelve, and began to send them out two by two; and he gave them authority over the unclean\nspirits. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 6:8"}, "He commanded them that they should take nothing for their journey, except a staff only: no bread, no wallet, no money in\ntheir purse, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 6:9"}, "but to wear sandals, and not put on two tunics. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 6:10"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWherever you enter into a house, stay there until you depart from there.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 6:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever will not receive you nor hear you, as you depart from there, shake off the dust that is under your feet for\na testimony against them. Assuredly, I tell you, it will be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgement than\nfor that city!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 6:12"}, "They went out and preached that people should repent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 6:13"}, "They cast out many demons, and anointed many with oil who were sick, and healed them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 6:14"}, "King Herod heard this, for his name had become known, and he said, \u201cYahya the Baptiser has risen from the dead, and\ntherefore these powers are at work in him.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 6:15"}, "But others said, \u201cHe is Ilyas.\u201d Others said, \u201cHe is a prophet, or like one of the prophets.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 6:16"}, "But Herod, when he heard this, said, \u201cThis is Yahya, whom I beheaded. He has risen from the dead.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 6:17"}, "For Herod himself had sent out and arrested Yahya, and bound him in prison for the sake of Herodias, his brother Philip\u2019s\nwife, for he had married her. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 6:18"}, "For Yahya said to Herod, \u201cIt is not lawful for you to have your brother\u2019s wife.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 6:19"}, "Herodias set herself against him, and desired to kill him, but she couldn\u2019t,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 6:20"}, "for Herod feared Yahya, knowing that he was a righteous and holy man, and kept him safe. When he heard him, he did many\nthings, and he heard him gladly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 6:21"}, "Then a convenient day came, that Herod on his birthday made a supper for his nobles, the high officers, and the chief men\nof Galilee. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 6:22"}, "When the daughter of Herodias herself came in and danced, she pleased Herod and those sitting with him. The king said to\nthe young lady, \u201cAsk me whatever you want, and I will give it to you.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 6:23"}, "He swore to her, \u201cWhatever you shall ask of me, I will give you, up to half of my kingdom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 6:24"}, "She went out, and said to her mother, \u201cWhat shall I ask?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["She said, \u201cThe head of Yahya the Baptiser.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 6:25"}, "She came in immediately with haste to the king, and asked, \u201cI want you to give me right now the head of Yahya the\nBaptiser on a platter.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 6:26"}, "The king was exceedingly sorry, but for the sake of his oaths, and of his dinner guests, he didn\u2019t wish to refuse her.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 6:27"}, "Immediately the king sent out a soldier of his guard, and commanded to bring Yahya\u2019s head, and he went and beheaded him\nin the prison, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 6:28"}, "and brought his head on a platter, and gave it to the young lady; and the young lady gave it to her mother.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 6:29"}, "When his disciples heard this, they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 6:30"}, "The apostles gathered themselves together to Isa, and they told him all things, whatever they had done, and whatever they\nhad taught. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 6:31"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou come apart into a deserted place, and rest\nawhile.\u201d"]}, " For there were many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 6:32"}, "They went away in the boat to a deserted place by themselves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 6:33"}, "They", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR reads \u201cThe multitudes\u201d instead of\n\u201cThey\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " saw them going, and many recognised him and ran there on foot from all the cities. They arrived before them and came\ntogether to him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 6:34"}, "Isa came out, saw a great multitude, and he had compassion on them, because they were like sheep without a shepherd, and\nhe began to teach them many things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 6:35"}, "When it was late in the day, his disciples came to him, and said, \u201cThis place is deserted, and it is late in the day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 6:36"}, "Send them away, that they may go into the surrounding country and villages, and buy themselves bread, for they have\nnothing to eat.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 6:37"}, "But he answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou give them something to eat.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They asked him, \u201cShall we go and buy two hundred denarii", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:37 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["200 denarii was about 7 or 8 months wages for an agricultural\nlabourer."]}], "caller": "+"}, " worth of bread, and give them something to eat?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 6:38"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow many loaves do you have? Go see.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["When they knew, they said, \u201cFive, and two fish.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 6:39"}, "He commanded them that everyone should sit down in groups on the green grass.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 6:40"}, "They sat down in ranks, by hundreds and by fifties. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 6:41"}, "He took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to heaven, he blessed and broke the loaves, and he gave to his\ndisciples to set before them, and he divided the two fish amongst them all.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 6:42"}, "They all ate, and were filled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 6:43"}, "They took up twelve baskets full of broken pieces and also of the fish.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 6:44"}, "Those who ate the loaves were", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:44 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cabout\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " five thousand men.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 6:45"}, "Immediately he made his disciples get into the boat, and to go ahead to the other side, to Bethsaida, while he himself\nsent the multitude away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MRK 6:46"}, "After he had taken leave of them, he went up the mountain to pray.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MRK 6:47"}, "When evening had come, the boat was in the middle of the sea, and he was alone on the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MRK 6:48"}, "Seeing them distressed in rowing, for the wind was contrary to them, about the fourth watch of the night he came to them,\nwalking on the sea, ", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["6:48 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["See Ayyub 9:8"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and he would have passed by them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MRK 6:49"}, "but they, when they saw him walking on the sea, supposed that it was a ghost, and cried out;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MRK 6:50"}, "for they all saw him, and were troubled. But he immediately spoke with them, and said to them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCheer up! It is I!"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:50 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, \u201cI AM!\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Don\u2019t be\nafraid.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MRK 6:51"}, "He got into the boat with them; and the wind ceased, and they were very amazed amongst themselves, and marvelled;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MRK 6:52"}, "for they hadn\u2019t understood about the loaves, but their hearts were hardened.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "MRK 6:53"}, "When they had crossed over, they came to land at Gennesaret, and moored to the shore.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "MRK 6:54"}, "When they had come out of the boat, immediately the people recognised him,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "MRK 6:55"}, "and ran around that whole region, and began to bring those who were sick, on their mats, to where they heard he was.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "MRK 6:56"}, "Wherever he entered, into villages, or into cities, or into the country, they laid the sick in the marketplaces, and\nbegged him that they might just touch the fringe", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["6:56 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\ntassel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of his garment; and as many as touched him were made well.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 7:1"}, "Then the Pharisees and some of the scribes gathered together to him, having come from Jerusalem.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 7:2"}, "Now when they saw some of his disciples eating bread with defiled, that is unwashed, hands, they found fault.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 7:3"}, "(For the Pharisees and all the Jews don\u2019t eat unless they wash their hands and forearms, holding to the tradition of the\nelders. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 7:4"}, "They don\u2019t eat when they come from the marketplace unless they bathe themselves, and there are many other things, which\nthey have received to hold to: washings of cups, pitchers, bronze vessels, and couches.)\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 7:5"}, "The Pharisees and the scribes asked him, \u201cWhy don\u2019t your disciples walk according to the tradition of the elders, but eat\ntheir bread with unwashed hands?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 7:6"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWell did Isaiah prophesy of you hypocrites, as it is\nwritten,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018This people honours me with their lips,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but their heart is far from me."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 7:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But they worship me in vain,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["teaching as doctrines the commandments of men.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:7 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 29:13 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 7:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor you set aside the commandment of Allah, and hold tightly to the tradition of men\u2014the washing of pitchers and\ncups, and you do many other such things.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 7:9"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFull well do you reject the commandment of Allah, that you may keep your tradition.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 7:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Musa said, \u2018Honour your father and your mother;\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:12; Deuteronomy 5:16"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and, \u2018He who speaks evil of father or mother, let him be put to\ndeath.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["7:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 21:17; Leviticus 20:9"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 7:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you say, \u2018If a man tells his father or his mother, \u201cWhatever profit you might have received from me is\nCorban,\u201d\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Corban is a Hebrew word for an offering devoted to\nAllah."]}], "caller": "+"}, " that is to say, given to Allah, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 7:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cthen you no longer allow him to do anything for his father or his mother,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 7:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["making void the word of Allah by your tradition, which you have handed down. You do many things like\nthis.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 7:14"}, "He called all the multitude to himself, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHear me, all of you, and understand.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 7:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["There is nothing from outside of the man, that going into him can defile him; but the things which proceed out of\nthe man are those that defile the man. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 7:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If anyone has ears to hear, let him hear!\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:16\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 16."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 7:17"}, "When he had entered into a house away from the multitude, his disciples asked him about the parable.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 7:18"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAre you also without understanding? Don\u2019t you perceive that whatever goes into the man from outside\ncan\u2019t defile him, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 7:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["because it doesn\u2019t go into his heart, but into his stomach, then into the latrine, making all foods\nclean?\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU ends Isa\u2019s direct quote and question after \u201clatrine\u201d, ending the verse with \u201cThus he declared\nall foods clean. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 7:20"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThat which proceeds out of the man, that defiles the man.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 7:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For from within, out of the hearts of men, proceed evil thoughts, adulteries, sexual sins, murders, thefts,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 7:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["covetings, wickedness, deceit, lustful desires, an evil eye, blasphemy, pride, and foolishness.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 7:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["All these evil things come from within, and defile the man.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 7:24"}, "From there he arose, and went away into the borders of Tyre and Sidon. He entered into a house, and didn\u2019t want anyone to\nknow it, but he couldn\u2019t escape notice. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 7:25"}, "For a woman, whose little daughter had an unclean spirit, having heard of him, came and fell down at his feet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 7:26"}, "Now the woman was a Greek, a Syrophoenician by race. She begged him that he would cast the demon out of her daughter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 7:27"}, "But Isa said to her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cLet the children be filled first, for it is not appropriate to take the children\u2019s bread and\nthrow it to the dogs.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 7:28"}, "But she answered him, \u201cYes, Lord. Yet even the dogs under the table eat the children\u2019s crumbs.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 7:29"}, "He said to her, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor this saying, go your way. The demon has gone out of your\ndaughter.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 7:30"}, "She went away to her house, and found the child having been laid on the bed, with the demon gone out.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 7:31"}, "Again he departed from the borders of Tyre and Sidon, and came to the sea of Galilee, through the middle of the region of\nDecapolis. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 7:32"}, "They brought to him one who was deaf and had an impediment in his speech. They begged him to lay his hand on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 7:33"}, "He took him aside from the multitude, privately, and put his fingers into his ears, and he spat, and touched his tongue.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 7:34"}, "Looking up to heaven, he sighed, and said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEphphatha!\u201d\n"]}, " that is, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBe opened!\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 7:35"}, "Immediately his ears were opened, and the impediment of his tongue was released, and he spoke clearly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 7:36"}, "He commanded them that they should tell no one, but the more he commanded them, so much the more widely they proclaimed\nit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 7:37"}, "They were astonished beyond measure, saying, \u201cHe has done all things well. He makes even the deaf hear, and the mute\nspeak!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 8:1"}, "In those days, when there was a very great multitude, and they had nothing to eat, Isa called his disciples to himself,\nand said to them, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 8:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI have compassion on the multitude, because they have stayed with me now three days, and have nothing to eat.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 8:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If I send them away fasting to their home, they will faint on the way, for some of them have come a long\nway.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 8:4"}, "His disciples answered him, \u201cFrom where could one satisfy these people with bread here in a deserted place?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 8:5"}, "He asked them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow many loaves do you have?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said, \u201cSeven.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 8:6"}, "He commanded the multitude to sit down on the ground, and he took the seven loaves. Having given thanks, he broke them,\nand gave them to his disciples to serve, and they served the multitude.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 8:7"}, "They had a few small fish. Having blessed them, he said to serve these also.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 8:8"}, "They ate, and were filled. They took up seven baskets of broken pieces that were left over.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 8:9"}, "Those who had eaten were about four thousand. Then he sent them away.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 8:10"}, "Immediately he entered into the boat with his disciples, and came into the region of Dalmanutha.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 8:11"}, "The Pharisees came out and began to question him, seeking from him a sign from heaven, and testing him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 8:12"}, "He sighed deeply in his spirit, and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy does this\ngeneration"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:12 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cgeneration\u201d here (genea) could also be translated \u201cpeople\u201d, \u201crace\u201d, or\n\u201cfamily\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["seek a sign? Most certainly I tell you, no sign will be given to this\ngeneration.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 8:13"}, "He left them, and again entering into the boat, departed to the other side.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 8:14"}, "They forgot to take bread; and they didn\u2019t have more than one loaf in the boat with them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 8:15"}, "He warned them, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake heed: beware of the yeast of the Pharisees and the yeast of\nHerod.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 8:16"}, "They reasoned with one another, saying, \u201cIt\u2019s because we have no bread.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 8:17"}, "Isa, perceiving it, said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you reason that it\u2019s because you have no bread? Don\u2019t you perceive yet,\nneither understand? Is your heart still hardened? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 8:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Having eyes, don\u2019t you see? Having ears, don\u2019t you hear? Don\u2019t you remember?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 8:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When I broke the five loaves amongst the five thousand, how many baskets full of broken pieces did you take\nup?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They told him, \u201cTwelve.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 8:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen the seven loaves fed the four thousand, how many baskets full of broken pieces did you take\nup?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They told him, \u201cSeven.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 8:21"}, "He asked them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t you understand yet?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 8:22"}, "He came to Bethsaida. They brought a blind man to him, and begged him to touch him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 8:23"}, "He took hold of the blind man by the hand, and brought him out of the village. When he had spat on his eyes, and laid his\nhands on him, he asked him if he saw anything. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 8:24"}, "He looked up, and said, \u201cI see men; for I see them like trees walking.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 8:25"}, "Then again he laid his hands on his eyes. He looked intently, and was restored, and saw everyone clearly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 8:26"}, "He sent him away to his house, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t enter into the village, nor tell anyone in the\nvillage.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 8:27"}, "Isa went out, with his disciples, into the villages of Caesarea Philippi. On the way he asked his disciples,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWho do men say that I am?\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 8:28"}, "They told him, \u201cYahya the Baptiser, and others say Ilyas, but others: one of the prophets.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 8:29"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBut who do you say that I am?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Peter answered, \u201cYou are the Masih.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 8:30"}, "He commanded them that they should tell no one about him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 8:31"}, "He began to teach them that the Son of Man must suffer many things, and be rejected by the elders, the chief priests, and\nthe scribes, and be killed, and after three days rise again. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 8:32"}, "He spoke to them openly. Peter took him, and began to rebuke him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 8:33"}, "But he, turning around, and seeing his disciples, rebuked Peter, and said,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGet behind me, Shaitan! For you have in mind not the things of Allah, but the things of\nmen.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 8:34"}, "He called the multitude to himself with his disciples, and said to them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhoever wants to come after me, let him deny himself, and take up his cross, and follow me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 8:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever wants to save his life will lose it; and whoever will lose his life for my sake and the sake of the Good\nNews will save it. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 8:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For what does it profit a man, to gain the whole world, and forfeit his life?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 8:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For what will a man give in exchange for his life? "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 8:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever will be ashamed of me and of my words in this adulterous and sinful generation, the Son of Man also will\nbe ashamed of him, when he comes in his Father\u2019s glory, with the holy\nangels.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 9:1"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, there are some standing here who will in no way taste death until they\nsee Allah\u2019s Kingdom come with power.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 9:2"}, "After six days Isa took with him Peter, Yaqub, and Yuhanna, and brought them up onto a high mountain privately by\nthemselves, and he was changed into another form in front of them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 9:3"}, "His clothing became glistening, exceedingly white, like snow, such as no launderer on earth can whiten them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 9:4"}, "Ilyas and Musa appeared to them, and they were talking with Isa.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 9:5"}, "Peter answered Isa, \u201cRabbi, it is good for us to be here. Let\u2019s make three tents: one for you, one for Musa, and one for\nIlyas.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 9:6"}, "For he didn\u2019t know what to say, for they were very afraid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 9:7"}, "A cloud came, overshadowing them, and a voice came out of the cloud, \u201cThis is my beloved Son. Listen to him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 9:8"}, "Suddenly looking around, they saw no one with them any more, except Isa only.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 9:9"}, "As they were coming down from the mountain, he commanded them that they should tell no one what things they had seen,\nuntil after the Son of Man had risen from the dead. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 9:10"}, "They kept this saying to themselves, questioning what the \u201crising from the dead\u201d meant.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 9:11"}, "They asked him, saying, \u201cWhy do the scribes say that Ilyas must come first?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 9:12"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIlyas indeed comes first, and restores all things. How is it written about the Son of Man, that he\nshould suffer many things and be despised? "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 9:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But I tell you that Ilyas has come, and they have also done to him whatever they wanted to, even as it is written\nabout him.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 9:14"}, "Coming to the disciples, he saw a great multitude around them, and scribes questioning them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 9:15"}, "Immediately all the multitude, when they saw him, were greatly amazed, and running to him, greeted him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 9:16"}, "He asked the scribes, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat are you asking them?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 9:17"}, "One of the multitude answered, \u201cTeacher, I brought to you my son, who has a mute spirit;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 9:18"}, "and wherever it seizes him, it throws him down, and he foams at the mouth, and grinds his teeth, and wastes away. I asked\nyour disciples to cast it out, and they weren\u2019t able.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 9:19"}, "He answered him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cUnbelieving generation, how long shall I be with you? How long shall I bear with you? Bring him to\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 9:20"}, "They brought him to him, and when he saw him, immediately the spirit convulsed him, and he fell on the ground, wallowing\nand foaming at the mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 9:21"}, "He asked his father, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow long has it been since this has come to\nhim?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said, \u201cFrom childhood. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 9:22"}, "Often it has cast him both into the fire and into the water to destroy him. But if you can do anything, have compassion\non us, and help us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 9:23"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf you can believe, all things are possible to him who\nbelieves.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 9:24"}, "Immediately the father of the child cried out with tears, \u201cI believe. Help my unbelief!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 9:25"}, "When Isa saw that a multitude came running together, he rebuked the unclean spirit, saying to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou mute and deaf spirit, I command you, come out of him, and never enter him\nagain!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 9:26"}, "After crying out and convulsing him greatly, it came out of him. The boy became like one dead, so much that most of them\nsaid, \u201cHe is dead.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 9:27"}, "But Isa took him by the hand, and raised him up; and he arose.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 9:28"}, "When he had come into the house, his disciples asked him privately, \u201cWhy couldn\u2019t we cast it out?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 9:29"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThis kind can come out by nothing, except by prayer and\nfasting.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 9:30"}, "They went out from there, and passed through Galilee. He didn\u2019t want anyone to know it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 9:31"}, "For he was teaching his disciples, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe Son of Man is being handed over to the hands of men, and\nthey will kill him; and when he is killed, on the third day he will rise\nagain.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 9:32"}, "But they didn\u2019t understand the saying, and were afraid to ask him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 9:33"}, "He came to Capernaum, and when he was in the house he asked them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat were you arguing amongst yourselves on the way?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 9:34"}, "But they were silent, for they had disputed with one another on the way about who was the greatest.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 9:35"}, "He sat down, and called the twelve; and he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIf any man wants to be first, he shall be last of all, and\nservant of all.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 9:36"}, "He took a little child, and set him in the middle of them. Taking him in his arms, he said to them,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 9:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhoever receives one such little child in my name, receives me, and whoever receives me, doesn\u2019t receive me, but\nhim who sent me.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 9:38"}, "Yuhanna said to him, \u201cTeacher, we saw someone who doesn\u2019t follow us casting out demons in your name; and we forbade him,\nbecause he doesn\u2019t follow us.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 9:39"}, "But Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t forbid him, for there is no one who will do a mighty work in my name, and be able quickly to\nspeak evil of me. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 9:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever is not against us is on our side. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 9:41"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For whoever will give you a cup of water to drink in my name, because you are Masih\u2019s, most certainly I tell you, he\nwill in no way lose his reward. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 9:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever will cause one of these little ones who believe in me to stumble, it would be better for him if he were\nthrown into the sea with a millstone hung around his neck. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 9:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your hand causes you to stumble, cut it off. It is better for you to enter into life maimed, rather than having\nyour two hands to go into Gehenna, "]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:43 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["into the unquenchable fire, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 9:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018where their worm doesn\u2019t die, and the fire is not quenched.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["9:44 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 66:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:44 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse\n44."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 9:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your foot causes you to stumble, cut it off. It is better for you to enter into life lame, rather than having\nyour two feet to be cast into Gehenna, "]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:45 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or,\nHell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["into the fire that will never be quenched\u2014"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MRK 9:46"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018where their worm doesn\u2019t die, and the fire is not quenched.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:46 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 46."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MRK 9:47"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If your eye causes you to stumble, cast it out. It is better for you to enter into Allah\u2019s Kingdom with one eye,\nrather than having two eyes to be cast into the Gehenna"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["9:47 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Hell"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["of fire, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MRK 9:48"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018where their worm doesn\u2019t die, and the fire is not quenched.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["9:48 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 66:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MRK 9:49"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For everyone will be salted with fire, and every sacrifice will be seasoned with salt.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MRK 9:50"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Salt is good, but if the salt has lost its saltiness, with what will you season it? Have salt in yourselves, and be\nat peace with one another.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 10:1"}, "He arose from there and came into the borders of Judea and beyond the Jordan. Multitudes came together to him again. As he\nusually did, he was again teaching them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 10:2"}, "Pharisees came to him testing him, and asked him, \u201cIs it lawful for a man to divorce his wife?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 10:3"}, "He answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat did Musa command you?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 10:4"}, "They said, \u201cMusa allowed a certificate of divorce to be written, and to divorce her.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 10:5"}, "But Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cFor your hardness of heart, he wrote you this commandment.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 10:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But from the beginning of the creation, Allah made them male and\nfemale."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis 1:27"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 10:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For this cause a man will leave his father and mother, and will join to his wife,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 10:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and the two will become one flesh,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Genesis\n2:24"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["so that they are no longer two, but one flesh. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 10:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What therefore Allah has joined together, let no man separate.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 10:10"}, "In the house, his disciples asked him again about the same matter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 10:11"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhoever divorces his wife, and marries another, commits adultery against her.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 10:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If a woman herself divorces her husband, and marries another, she commits\nadultery.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 10:13"}, "They were bringing to him little children, that he should touch them, but the disciples rebuked those who were bringing\nthem. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 10:14"}, "But when Isa saw it, he was moved with indignation, and said to them,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAllow the little children to come to me! Don\u2019t forbid them, for Allah\u2019s Kingdom belongs to such as these.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 10:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, whoever will not receive Allah\u2019s Kingdom like a little child, he will in no way enter\ninto it.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 10:16"}, "He took them in his arms, and blessed them, laying his hands on them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 10:17"}, "As he was going out into the way, one ran to him, knelt before him, and asked him, \u201cGood Teacher, what shall I do that I\nmay inherit eternal life?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 10:18"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you call me good? No one is good except one\u2014Allah.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 10:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You know the commandments: \u2018Do not murder,\u2019 \u2018Do not commit adultery,\u2019 \u2018Do not steal,\u2019 \u2018Do not give false testimony,\u2019\n\u2018Do not defraud,\u2019 \u2018Honour your father and mother.\u2019\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["10:19\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 20:12-16; Deuteronomy 5:16-20 "]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 10:20"}, "He said to him, \u201cTeacher, I have observed all these things from my youth.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 10:21"}, "Isa looking at him loved him, and said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cOne thing you lack. Go, sell whatever you have, and give to the poor,\nand you will have treasure in heaven; and come, follow me, taking up the\ncross.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 10:22"}, "But his face fell at that saying, and he went away sorrowful, for he was one who had great possessions.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 10:23"}, "Isa looked around, and said to his disciples, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow difficult it is for those who have riches to enter into Allah\u2019s\nKingdom!\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 10:24"}, "The disciples were amazed at his words. But Isa answered again,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cChildren, how hard it is for those who trust in riches to enter into Allah\u2019s Kingdom!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 10:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It is easier for a camel to go through a needle\u2019s eye than for a rich man to enter into Allah\u2019s\nKingdom.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 10:26"}, "They were exceedingly astonished, saying to him, \u201cThen who can be saved?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 10:27"}, "Isa, looking at them, said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWith men it is impossible, but not with Allah, for all things are possible with\nAllah.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 10:28"}, "Peter began to tell him, \u201cBehold, we have left all, and have followed you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 10:29"}, "Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, there is no one who has left house, or brothers, or sisters, or father, or\nmother, or wife, or children, or land, for my sake, and for the sake of the Good News,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 10:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but he will receive one hundred times more now in this time: houses, brothers, sisters, mothers, children, and land,\nwith persecutions; and in the age to come eternal life. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 10:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But many who are first will be last; and the last first.\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 10:32"}, "They were on the way, going up to Jerusalem; and Isa was going in front of them, and they were amazed; and those who\nfollowed were afraid. He again took the twelve, and began to tell them the things that were going to happen to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 10:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, we are going up to Jerusalem. The Son of Man will be delivered to the chief priests and the scribes. They\nwill condemn him to death, and will deliver him to the Gentiles.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 10:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["They will mock him, spit on him, scourge him, and kill him. On the third day he will rise\nagain.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 10:35"}, "Yaqub and Yuhanna, the sons of Zebedee, came near to him, saying, \u201cTeacher, we want you to do for us whatever we will\nask.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 10:36"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you want me to do for you?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 10:37"}, "They said to him, \u201cGrant to us that we may sit, one at your right hand, and one at your left hand, in your glory.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 10:38"}, "But Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou don\u2019t know what you are asking. Are you able to drink the cup that I drink, and to be\nbaptised with the baptism that I am baptised with?\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 10:39"}, "They said to him, \u201cWe are able.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou shall indeed drink the cup that I drink, and you shall be baptised with the baptism that I am\nbaptised with; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 10:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["but to sit at my right hand and at my left hand is not mine to give, but for whom it has been\nprepared.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 10:41"}, "When the ten heard it, they began to be indignant towards Yaqub and Yuhanna.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 10:42"}, "Isa summoned them, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou know that they who are recognised as rulers over the nations lord it over\nthem, and their great ones exercise authority over them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 10:43"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But it shall not be so amongst you, but whoever wants to become great amongst you shall be your servant.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 10:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whoever of you wants to become first amongst you, shall be bondservant of all.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 10:45"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Son of Man also came not to be served, but to serve, and to give his life as a ransom for\nmany.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MRK 10:46"}, "They came to Jericho. As he went out from Jericho, with his disciples and a great multitude, the son of Timaeus,\nBartimaeus, a blind beggar, was sitting by the road. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MRK 10:47"}, "When he heard that it was Isa the Nazarene, he began to cry out, and say, \u201cIsa, you son of Dawood, have mercy on me!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MRK 10:48"}, "Many rebuked him, that he should be quiet, but he cried out much more, \u201cYou son of Dawood, have mercy on me!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MRK 10:49"}, "Isa stood still, and said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cCall him.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They called the blind man, saying to him, \u201cCheer up! Get up. He is calling you!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MRK 10:50"}, "He, casting away his cloak, sprang up, and came to Isa. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MRK 10:51"}, "Isa asked him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhat do you want me to do for you?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The blind man said to him, \u201cRabboni,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["10:51 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Rabboni is a transliteration of the Hebrew word for \u201cgreat\nteacher.\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " that I may see again.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MRK 10:52"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo your way. Your faith has made you well.\u201d\n"]}, " Immediately he received his sight, and followed Isa on the way.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 11:1"}, "When they came near to Jerusalem, to Bethsphage", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:1\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR & NU read \u201cBethphage\u201d instead of \u201cBethsphage\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and Bethany, at the Mount of Olives, he sent two of his disciples,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 11:2"}, "and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo your way into the village that is opposite you. Immediately as you enter into it, you will find\na young donkey tied, on which no one has sat. Untie him, and bring him.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 11:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["If anyone asks you, \u2018Why are you doing this?\u2019 say, \u2018The Lord needs him;\u2019 and immediately he will send him back\nhere.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 11:4"}, "They went away, and found a young donkey tied at the door outside in the open street, and they untied him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 11:5"}, "Some of those who stood there asked them, \u201cWhat are you doing, untying the young donkey?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 11:6"}, "They said to them just as Isa had said, and they let them go.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 11:7"}, "They brought the young donkey to Isa, and threw their garments on it, and Isa sat on it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 11:8"}, "Many spread their garments on the way, and others were cutting down branches from the trees, and spreading them on the\nroad. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 11:9"}, "Those who went in front, and those who followed, cried out, \u201cHosanna!\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cHosanna\u201d means \u201csave us\u201d or \u201chelp us, we pray\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " Blessed is he who comes in the name of the\nLord!", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 118:25-26"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 11:10"}, "Blessed is the kingdom of our father Dawood that is coming in the name of the Lord! Hosanna in the highest!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 11:11"}, "Isa entered into the temple in Jerusalem. When he had looked around at everything, it being now evening, he went out to\nBethany with the twelve. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 11:12"}, "The next day, when they had come out from Bethany, he was hungry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 11:13"}, "Seeing a fig tree afar off having leaves, he came to see if perhaps he might find anything on it. When he came to it, he\nfound nothing but leaves, for it was not the season for figs. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 11:14"}, "Isa told it, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMay no one ever eat fruit from you again!\u201d\n"]}, " and his disciples heard it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 11:15"}, "They came to Jerusalem, and Isa entered into the temple, and began to throw out those who sold and those who bought in\nthe temple, and overthrew the money changers\u2019 tables, and the seats of those who sold the doves.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 11:16"}, "He would not allow anyone to carry a container through the temple.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 11:17"}, "He taught, saying to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIsn\u2019t it written, \u2018My house will be called a house of prayer for all the\nnations?\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 56:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you have made it a den of\nrobbers!\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["11:17 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Jeremiah 7:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 11:18"}, "The chief priests and the scribes heard it, and sought how they might destroy him. For they feared him, because all the\nmultitude was astonished at his teaching. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 11:19"}, "When evening came, he went out of the city. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 11:20"}, "As they passed by in the morning, they saw the fig tree withered away from the roots.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 11:21"}, "Peter, remembering, said to him, \u201cRabbi, look! The fig tree which you cursed has withered away.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 11:22"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHave faith in Allah. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 11:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For most certainly I tell you, whoever may tell this mountain, \u2018Be taken up and cast into the sea,\u2019 and doesn\u2019t\ndoubt in his heart, but believes that what he says is happening; he shall have whatever he says.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 11:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore I tell you, all things whatever you pray and ask for, believe that you have received them, and you shall\nhave them. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 11:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Whenever you stand praying, forgive, if you have anything against anyone; so that your Father, who is in heaven, may\nalso forgive you your transgressions. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 11:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But if you do not forgive, neither will your Father in heaven forgive your\ntransgressions.\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["11:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 26."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 11:27"}, "They came again to Jerusalem, and as he was walking in the temple, the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders came to\nhim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 11:28"}, "and they began saying to him, \u201cBy what authority do you do these things? Or who gave you this authority to do these\nthings?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 11:29"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI will ask you one question. Answer me, and I will tell you by what authority I do these things.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 11:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The baptism of Yahya\u2014was it from heaven, or from men? Answer me.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 11:31"}, "They reasoned with themselves, saying, \u201cIf we should say, \u2018From heaven;\u2019 he will say, \u2018Why then did you not believe him?\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 11:32"}, "If we should say, \u2018From men\u2019\u201d\u2014they feared the people, for all held Yahya to really be a prophet.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 11:33"}, "They answered Isa, \u201cWe don\u2019t know.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNeither do I tell you by what authority I do these\nthings.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 12:1"}, "He began to speak to them in parables. ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cA man planted a vineyard, put a hedge around it, dug a pit for the wine press,\nbuilt a tower, rented it out to a farmer, and went into another country.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 12:2"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When it was time, he sent a servant to the farmer to get from the farmer his share of the fruit of the vineyard.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 12:3"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["They took him, beat him, and sent him away empty. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 12:4"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again, he sent another servant to them; and they threw stones at him, wounded him in the head, and sent him away\nshamefully treated. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 12:5"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Again he sent another; and they killed him; and many others, beating some, and killing some.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 12:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore still having one, his beloved son, he sent him last to them, saying, \u2018They will respect my son.\u2019\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 12:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But those farmers said amongst themselves, \u2018This is the heir. Come, let\u2019s kill him, and the inheritance will be\nours.\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 12:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["They took him, killed him, and cast him out of the vineyard.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 12:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What therefore will the lord of the vineyard do? He will come and destroy the farmers, and will give the vineyard to\nothers. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 12:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Haven\u2019t you even read this Scripture:"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018The stone which the builders rejected"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["was made the head of the corner."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 12:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["This was from the Lord."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["It is marvellous in our eyes\u2019?\u201d"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur\n118:22-23"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 12:12"}, "They tried to seize him, but they feared the multitude; for they perceived that he spoke the parable against them. They\nleft him, and went away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 12:13"}, "They sent some of the Pharisees and the Herodians to him, that they might trap him with words.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 12:14"}, "When they had come, they asked him, \u201cTeacher, we know that you are honest, and don\u2019t defer to anyone; for you aren\u2019t\npartial to anyone, but truly teach the way of Allah. Is it lawful to pay taxes to Caesar, or not?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 12:15"}, "Shall we give, or shall we not give?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But he, knowing their hypocrisy, said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhy do you test me? Bring me a denarius, that I may see\nit.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 12:16"}, "They brought it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhose is this image and inscription?\u201d"]}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They said to him, \u201cCaesar\u2019s.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 12:17"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cRender to Caesar the things that are Caesar\u2019s, and to Allah the things that are\nAllah\u2019s.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They marvelled greatly at him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 12:18"}, "Some Sadducees, who say that there is no resurrection, came to him. They asked him, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 12:19"}, "\u201cTeacher, Musa wrote to us, \u2018If a man\u2019s brother dies, and leaves a wife behind him, and leaves no children, that his\nbrother should take his wife, and raise up offspring for his brother.\u2019\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 12:20"}, "There were seven brothers. The first took a wife, and dying left no offspring.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 12:21"}, "The second took her, and died, leaving no children behind him. The third likewise;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 12:22"}, "and the seven took her and left no children. Last of all the woman also died.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 12:23"}, "In the resurrection, when they rise, whose wife will she be of them? For the seven had her as a wife.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 12:24"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIsn\u2019t this because you are mistaken, not knowing the Scriptures, nor the power of Allah?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 12:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For when they will rise from the dead, they neither marry, nor are given in marriage, but are like angels in heaven.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 12:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But about the dead, that they are raised; haven\u2019t you read in the book of Musa, about the Bush, how Allah spoke to\nhim, saying, \u2018I am Allah of Ibrahim, Allah of Is\u1e25\u0101q, and Allah of\nYaqub\u2019?"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:26 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Exodus 3:6"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 12:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He is not Allah of the dead, but of the living. You are therefore badly\nmistaken.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 12:28"}, "One of the scribes came, and heard them questioning together, and knowing that he had answered them well, asked him,\n\u201cWhich commandment is the greatest of all?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 12:29"}, "Isa answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThe greatest is, \u2018Hear, Israel, the Lord our Allah, the Lord is one:\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 12:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["you shall love Allah your Lord with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your mind, and with all\nyour strength.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Deuteronomy 6:4-5"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["This is the first commandment.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 12:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The second is like this, \u2018You shall love your neighbour as\nyourself.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:31 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Leviticus 19:18"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["There is no other commandment greater than\nthese.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 12:32"}, "The scribe said to him, \u201cTruly, teacher, you have said well that he is one, and there is none other but he,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 12:33"}, "and to love him with all the heart, and with all the understanding, with all the soul, and with all the strength, and to\nlove his neighbour as himself, is more important than all whole burnt offerings and sacrifices.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 12:34"}, "When Isa saw that he answered wisely, he said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cYou are not far from Allah\u2019s\nKingdom.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["No one dared ask him any question after that. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 12:35"}, "Isa responded, as he taught in the temple, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHow is it that the scribes say that the Masih is the son of Dawood?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 12:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For Dawood himself said in the Holy Spirit,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u2018The Lord said to my Lord,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSit at my right hand,"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["until I make your enemies the footstool of your feet.\u201d\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["12:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 110:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 12:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Therefore Dawood himself calls him Lord, so how can he be his son?\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["The common people heard him gladly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 12:38"}, "In his teaching he said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBeware of the scribes, who like to walk in long robes, and to get greetings in the\nmarketplaces, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 12:39"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and the best seats in the synagogues, and the best places at feasts:\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 12:40"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["those who devour widows\u2019 houses, and for a pretence make long prayers. These will receive greater\ncondemnation.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 12:41"}, "Isa sat down opposite the treasury, and saw how the multitude cast money into the treasury. Many who were rich cast in\nmuch. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 12:42"}, "A poor widow came, and she cast in two small brass coins,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:42 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, lepta (or widow\u2019s mites). Lepta are very small brass coins worth half a quadrans each, which is a\nquarter of the copper assarion. Lepta are worth less than 1% of an agricultural worker\u2019s daily\nwages."]}], "caller": "+"}, " which equal a quadrans coin.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["12:42 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A quadrans is a coin worth about 1/64 of a denarius. A denarius is\nabout one day\u2019s wages for an agricultural labourer."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 12:43"}, "He called his disciples to himself, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, this poor widow gave more than all\nthose who are giving into the treasury, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 12:44"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["for they all gave out of their abundance, but she, out of her poverty, gave all that she had to live\non.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 13:1"}, "As he went out of the temple, one of his disciples said to him, \u201cTeacher, see what kind of stones and what kind of\nbuildings!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 13:2"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cDo you see these great buildings? There will not be left here one stone on another, which will not\nbe thrown down.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 13:3"}, "As he sat on the Mount of Olives opposite the temple, Peter, Yaqub, Yuhanna, and Andreas asked him privately,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 13:4"}, "\u201cTell us, when will these things be? What is the sign that these things are all about to be fulfilled?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 13:5"}, "Isa, answering, began to tell them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBe careful that no one leads you astray.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 13:6"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For many will come in my name, saying, \u2018I am he!\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, \u201cI AM!\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and will lead many astray."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 13:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cWhen you hear of wars and rumours of wars, don\u2019t be troubled. For those must happen, but the end is not yet.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 13:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For nation will rise against nation, and kingdom against kingdom. There will be earthquakes in various places. There\nwill be famines and troubles. These things are the beginning of birth pains.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 13:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But watch yourselves, for they will deliver you up to councils. You will be beaten in synagogues. You will stand\nbefore rulers and kings for my sake, for a testimony to them. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 13:10"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["The Good News must first be preached to all the nations.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 13:11"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["When they lead you away and deliver you up, don\u2019t be anxious beforehand, or premeditate what you will say, but say\nwhatever will be given you in that hour. For it is not you who speak, but the Holy\nSpirit."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 13:12"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBrother will deliver up brother to death, and the father his child. Children will rise up against parents, and\ncause them to be put to death. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 13:13"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["You will be hated by all men for my name\u2019s sake, but he who endures to the end will be saved.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 13:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But when you see the abomination of desolation,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Daniel 9:17; 11:31; 12:11"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["spoken of by Daniel the prophet, standing where it ought\nnot\u201d"]}, " (let the reader understand), ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cthen let those who are in Judea flee to the mountains,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 13:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and let him who is on the housetop not go down, nor enter in, to take anything out of his house.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 13:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Let him who is in the field not return back to take his cloak.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 13:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But woe to those who are with child and to those who nurse babies in those days!\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 13:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Pray that your flight won\u2019t be in the winter. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 13:19"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For in those days there will be oppression, such as there has not been the like from the beginning of the creation\nwhich Allah created until now, and never will be. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 13:20"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Unless the Lord had shortened the days, no flesh would have been saved; but for the sake of the chosen ones, whom he\npicked out, he shortened the days. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 13:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then if anyone tells you, \u2018Look, here is the Masih!\u2019 or, \u2018Look, there!\u2019 don\u2019t believe it.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 13:22"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For there will arise false christs and false prophets, and will show signs and wonders, that they may lead astray,\nif possible, even the chosen ones. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 13:23"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But you watch."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBehold, I have told you all things beforehand. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 13:24"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But in those days, after that oppression, the sun will be darkened, the moon will not give its light,\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 13:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["the stars will be falling from the sky, and the powers that are in the heavens will be\nshaken."]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["13:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Isaiah 13:10; 34:4"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 13:26"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then they will see the Son of Man coming in clouds with great power and glory.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 13:27"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Then he will send out his angels, and will gather together his chosen ones from the four winds, from the ends of the\nearth to the ends of the sky."]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 13:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cNow from the fig tree, learn this parable. When the branch has now become tender, and produces its leaves, you know\nthat the summer is near; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 13:29"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["even so you also, when you see these things coming to pass, know that it is near, at the doors.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 13:30"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I say to you, this generation"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["13:30 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cgeneration\u201d (genea) could also be translated \u201crace\u201d, \u201cfamily\u201d, or\n\u201cpeople\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["will not pass away until all these things happen.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 13:31"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Heaven and earth will pass away, but my words will not pass away.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 13:32"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["But of that day or that hour no one knows, not even the angels in heaven, nor the Son, but only the Father.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 13:33"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch, keep alert, and pray; for you don\u2019t know when the time is.\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 13:34"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt is like a man, travelling to another country, having left his house, and given authority to his servants, and to\neach one his work, and also commanded the doorkeeper to keep watch.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 13:35"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch therefore, for you don\u2019t know when the lord of the house is coming, whether at evening, or at midnight, or\nwhen the rooster crows, or in the morning; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 13:36"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["lest coming suddenly he might find you sleeping. "]}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 13:37"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["What I tell you, I tell all: Watch.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 14:1"}, "It was now two days before the feast of the Passover and the unleavened bread, and the chief priests and the scribes\nsought how they might seize him by deception, and kill him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 14:2"}, "For they said, \u201cNot during the feast, because there might be a riot amongst the people.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 14:3"}, "While he was at Bethany, in the house of Shima\u2019un the leper, as he sat at the table, a woman came having an alabaster jar\nof ointment of pure nard\u2014very costly. She broke the jar, and poured it over his head.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 14:4"}, "But there were some who were indignant amongst themselves, saying, \u201cWhy has this ointment been wasted?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 14:5"}, "For this might have been sold for more than three hundred denarii,\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["300 denarii was about a year\u2019s wages for an agricultural labourer.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and given to the poor.\u201d So they grumbled against her. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 14:6"}, "But Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cLeave her alone. Why do you trouble her? She has done a good work for me.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 14:7"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For you always have the poor with you, and whenever you want to, you can do them good; but you will not always have\nme. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 14:8"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["She has done what she could. She has anointed my body beforehand for the burying.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 14:9"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, wherever this Good News may be preached throughout the whole world, that which this woman\nhas done will also be spoken of for a memorial of her.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 14:10"}, "Yehuda Iscariot, who was one of the twelve, went away to the chief priests, that he might deliver him to them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 14:11"}, "They, when they heard it, were glad, and promised to give him money. He sought how he might conveniently deliver him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 14:12"}, "On the first day of unleavened bread, when they sacrificed the Passover, his disciples asked him, \u201cWhere do you want us\nto go and prepare that you may eat the Passover?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 14:13"}, "He sent two of his disciples, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo into the city, and there you will meet a man carrying a pitcher\nof water. Follow him, "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 14:14"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["and wherever he enters in, tell the master of the house, \u2018The Teacher says, \u201cWhere is the guest room, where I may\neat the Passover with my disciples?\u201d\u2019 "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 14:15"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He will himself show you a large upper room furnished and ready. Get ready for us\nthere.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 14:16"}, "His disciples went out, and came into the city, and found things as he had said to them, and they prepared the Passover.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 14:17"}, "When it was evening he came with the twelve. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 14:18"}, "As they sat and were eating, Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, one of you will betray me\u2014he who eats with\nme.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 14:19"}, "They began to be sorrowful, and to ask him one by one, \u201cSurely not I?\u201d And another said, \u201cSurely not I?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 14:20"}, "He answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cIt is one of the twelve, he who dips with me in the dish.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 14:21"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["For the Son of Man goes, even as it is written about him, but woe to that man by whom the Son of Man is betrayed! It\nwould be better for that man if he had not been born.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 14:22"}, "As they were eating, Isa took bread, and when he had blessed, he broke it, and gave to them, and said,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cTake, eat. This is my body.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 14:23"}, "He took the cup, and when he had given thanks, he gave to them. They all drank of it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 14:24"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cThis is my blood of the new covenant, which is poured out for many.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 14:25"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Most certainly I tell you, I will no more drink of the fruit of the vine, until that day when I drink it anew in\nAllah\u2019s Kingdom.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 14:26"}, "When they had sung a hymn, they went out to the Mount of Olives.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 14:27"}, "Isa said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAll of you will be made to stumble because of me tonight, for it is written, \u2018I will strike the\nshepherd, and the sheep will be scattered.\u2019"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["14:27 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zakariya\n13:7"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 14:28"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["However, after I am raised up, I will go before you into Galilee.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 14:29"}, "But Peter said to him, \u201cAlthough all will be offended, yet I will not.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 14:30"}, "Isa said to him, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMost certainly I tell you, that you today, even this night, before the rooster crows twice, you\nwill deny me three times.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 14:31"}, "But he spoke all the more, \u201cIf I must die with you, I will not deny you.\u201d They all said the same thing.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 14:32"}, "They came to a place which was named Gethsemane. He said to his disciples,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSit here, while I pray.\u201d"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 14:33"}, "He took with him Peter, Yaqub, and Yuhanna, and began to be greatly troubled and distressed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 14:34"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy soul is exceedingly sorrowful, even to death. Stay here, and\nwatch.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 14:35"}, "He went forward a little, and fell on the ground, and prayed that, if it were possible, the hour might pass away from\nhim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 14:36"}, "He said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cAbba,"]}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:36 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Abba is a Greek spelling for the Aramaic word for \u201cFather\u201d or \u201cDaddy\u201d used in\na familiar, respectful, and loving way. "]}], "caller": "+"}, " ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Father, all things are possible to you. Please remove this cup from me.\nHowever, not what I desire, but what you desire.\u201d "]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 14:37"}, "He came and found them sleeping, and said to Peter, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cShima\u2019un, are you sleeping? Couldn\u2019t you watch one hour?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 14:38"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Watch and pray, that you may not enter into temptation. The spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is\nweak.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 14:39"}, "Again he went away, and prayed, saying the same words. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 14:40"}, "Again he returned, and found them sleeping, for their eyes were very heavy, and they didn\u2019t know what to answer him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 14:41"}, "He came the third time, and said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSleep on now, and take your rest. It is enough. The hour has come. Behold,\nthe Son of Man is betrayed into the hands of sinners. "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 14:42"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["Arise! Let\u2019s get going. Behold: he who betrays me is at hand.\u201d\n"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 14:43"}, "Immediately, while he was still speaking, Yehuda, one of the twelve, came\u2014and with him a multitude with swords and clubs,\nfrom the chief priests, the scribes, and the elders. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 14:44"}, "Now he who betrayed him had given them a sign, saying, \u201cWhomever I will kiss, that is he. Seize him, and lead him away\nsafely.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 14:45"}, "When he had come, immediately he came to him, and said, \u201cRabbi! Rabbi!\u201d and kissed him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MRK 14:46"}, "They laid their hands on him, and seized him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MRK 14:47"}, "But a certain one of those who stood by drew his sword, and struck the servant of the high priest, and cut off his ear.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "48", "sid": "MRK 14:48"}, "Isa answered them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cHave you come out, as against a robber, with swords and clubs to seize me?\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "49", "sid": "MRK 14:49"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["I was daily with you in the temple teaching, and you didn\u2019t arrest me. But this is so that the Scriptures might be\nfulfilled.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "50", "sid": "MRK 14:50"}, "They all left him, and fled. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "51", "sid": "MRK 14:51"}, "A certain young man followed him, having a linen cloth thrown around himself over his naked body. The young men grabbed\nhim, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "52", "sid": "MRK 14:52"}, "but he left the linen cloth, and fled from them naked. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "53", "sid": "MRK 14:53"}, "They led Isa away to the high priest. All the chief priests, the elders, and the scribes came together with him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "54", "sid": "MRK 14:54"}, "Peter had followed him from a distance, until he came into the court of the high priest. He was sitting with the\nofficers, and warming himself in the light of the fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "55", "sid": "MRK 14:55"}, "Now the chief priests and the whole council sought witnesses against Isa to put him to death, and found none.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "56", "sid": "MRK 14:56"}, "For many gave false testimony against him, and their testimony didn\u2019t agree with each other.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "57", "sid": "MRK 14:57"}, "Some stood up, and gave false testimony against him, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "58", "sid": "MRK 14:58"}, "\u201cWe heard him say, \u2018I will destroy this temple that is made with hands, and in three days I will build another made\nwithout hands.\u2019\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "59", "sid": "MRK 14:59"}, "Even so, their testimony didn\u2019t agree. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "60", "sid": "MRK 14:60"}, "The high priest stood up in the middle, and asked Isa, \u201cHave you no answer? What is it which these testify against you?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "61", "sid": "MRK 14:61"}, "But he stayed quiet, and answered nothing. Again the high priest asked him, \u201cAre you the Masih, the Son of the Blessed?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "62", "sid": "MRK 14:62"}, "Isa said, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cI am. You will see the Son of Man sitting at the right hand of Power, and coming with the clouds of the\nsky.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "63", "sid": "MRK 14:63"}, "The high priest tore his clothes, and said, \u201cWhat further need have we of witnesses?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "64", "sid": "MRK 14:64"}, "You have heard the blasphemy! What do you think?\u201d They all condemned him to be worthy of death.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "65", "sid": "MRK 14:65"}, "Some began to spit on him, and to cover his face, and to beat him with fists, and to tell him, \u201cProphesy!\u201d The officers\nstruck him with the palms of their hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "66", "sid": "MRK 14:66"}, "As Peter was in the courtyard below, one of the maids of the high priest came,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "67", "sid": "MRK 14:67"}, "and seeing Peter warming himself, she looked at him, and said, \u201cYou were also with the Nazarene, Isa!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "68", "sid": "MRK 14:68"}, "But he denied it, saying, \u201cI neither know, nor understand what you are saying.\u201d He went out on the porch, and the rooster\ncrowed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "69", "sid": "MRK 14:69"}, "The maid saw him, and began again to tell those who stood by, \u201cThis is one of them.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "70", "sid": "MRK 14:70"}, "But he again denied it. After a little while again those who stood by said to Peter, \u201cYou truly are one of them, for you\nare a Galilean, and your speech shows it.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "71", "sid": "MRK 14:71"}, "But he began to curse, and to swear, \u201cI don\u2019t know this man of whom you speak!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "72", "sid": "MRK 14:72"}, "The rooster crowed the second time. Peter remembered the word, how that Isa said to him,\n", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cBefore the rooster crows twice, you will deny me three times.\u201d"]}, " When he thought about that, he wept.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 15:1"}, "Immediately in the morning the chief priests, with the elders and scribes, and the whole council, held a consultation,\nbound Isa, carried him away, and delivered him up to Pilate. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 15:2"}, "Pilate asked him, \u201cAre you the King of the Jews?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cSo you say.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 15:3"}, "The chief priests accused him of many things. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 15:4"}, "Pilate again asked him, \u201cHave you no answer? See how many things they testify against you!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 15:5"}, "But Isa made no further answer, so that Pilate marvelled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 15:6"}, "Now at the feast he used to release to them one prisoner, whom they asked of him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 15:7"}, "There was one called Barabbas, bound with his fellow insurgents, men who in the insurrection had committed murder.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 15:8"}, "The multitude, crying aloud, began to ask him to do as he always did for them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 15:9"}, "Pilate answered them, saying, \u201cDo you want me to release to you the King of the Jews?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 15:10"}, "For he perceived that for envy the chief priests had delivered him up.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 15:11"}, "But the chief priests stirred up the multitude, that he should release Barabbas to them instead.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 15:12"}, "Pilate again asked them, \u201cWhat then should I do to him whom you call the King of the Jews?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 15:13"}, "They cried out again, \u201cCrucify him!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 15:14"}, "Pilate said to them, \u201cWhy, what evil has he done?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But they cried out exceedingly, \u201cCrucify him!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 15:15"}, "Pilate, wishing to please the multitude, released Barabbas to them, and handed over Isa, when he had flogged him, to be\ncrucified. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 15:16"}, "The soldiers led him away within the court, which is the Praetorium; and they called together the whole cohort.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 15:17"}, "They clothed him with purple, and weaving a crown of thorns, they put it on him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 15:18"}, "They began to salute him, \u201cHail, King of the Jews!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 15:19"}, "They struck his head with a reed, and spat on him, and bowing their knees, did homage to him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 15:20"}, "When they had mocked him, they took the purple off him, and put his own garments on him. They led him out to crucify him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "MRK 15:21"}, "They compelled one passing by, coming from the country, Shima\u2019un of Cyrene, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to go with\nthem, that he might bear his cross. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "MRK 15:22"}, "They brought him to the place called Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, \u201cThe place of a skull.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "MRK 15:23"}, "They offered him wine mixed with myrrh to drink, but he didn\u2019t take it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "MRK 15:24"}, "Crucifying him, they parted his garments amongst them, casting lots on them, what each should take.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "MRK 15:25"}, "It was the third hour, ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["9:00 a.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and they crucified him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "MRK 15:26"}, "The superscription of his accusation was written over him, \u201cTHE KING OF THE JEWS.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "MRK 15:27"}, "With him they crucified two robbers; one on his right hand, and one on his left.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "MRK 15:28"}, "The Scripture was fulfilled, which says, \u201cHe was counted with transgressors.\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:28 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU omits verse 28."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "MRK 15:29"}, "Those who passed by blasphemed him, wagging their heads, and saying, \u201cHa! You who destroy the temple, and build it in\nthree days, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "MRK 15:30"}, "save yourself, and come down from the cross!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "MRK 15:31"}, "Likewise, also the chief priests mocking amongst themselves with the scribes said, \u201cHe saved others. He can\u2019t save\nhimself. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "MRK 15:32"}, "Let the Masih, the King of Israel, now come down from the cross, that we may see and believe him.\u201d\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:32 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR omits \u201chim\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " Those who were crucified with him also insulted him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "MRK 15:33"}, "When the sixth hour ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, noon"]}], "caller": "+"}, " had come, there was darkness over the whole land until the ninth\nhour. ", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["15:33 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["3:00 p.m."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "MRK 15:34"}, "At the ninth hour Isa cried with a loud voice, saying, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cEloi, Eloi, lama\nsabachthani?\u201d"]}, " which is, being interpreted, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cMy Allah, my Allah, why have you forsaken\nme?\u201d"]}, " ", {"type": "note", "marker": "x", "content": [{"type": "char", "marker": "xo", "content": ["15:34 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "xt", "content": ["Zabur 22:1"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "MRK 15:35"}, "Some of those who stood by, when they heard it, said, \u201cBehold, he is calling Ilyas.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "MRK 15:36"}, "One ran, and filling a sponge full of vinegar, put it on a reed, and gave it to him to drink, saying, \u201cLet him be. Let\u2019s\nsee whether Ilyas comes to take him down.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "MRK 15:37"}, "Isa cried out with a loud voice, and gave up the spirit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "MRK 15:38"}, "The veil of the temple was torn in two from the top to the bottom.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "39", "sid": "MRK 15:39"}, "When the centurion, who stood by opposite him, saw that he cried out like this and breathed his last, he said, \u201cTruly\nthis man was the Son of Allah!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "40", "sid": "MRK 15:40"}, "There were also women watching from afar, amongst whom were both Maryam Magdalene, and Maryam the mother of Yaqub the\nless and of Joses, and Salome; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "41", "sid": "MRK 15:41"}, "who, when he was in Galilee, followed him and served him; and many other women who came up with him to Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "42", "sid": "MRK 15:42"}, "When evening had now come, because it was the Preparation Day, that is, the day before the Sabbath,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "43", "sid": "MRK 15:43"}, "Yusuf of Arimathaea, a prominent council member who also himself was looking for Allah\u2019s Kingdom, came. He boldly went in\nto Pilate, and asked for Isa\u2019s body. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "44", "sid": "MRK 15:44"}, "Pilate marvelled if he were already dead; and summoning the centurion, he asked him whether he had been dead long.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "45", "sid": "MRK 15:45"}, "When he found out from the centurion, he granted the body to Yusuf.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "46", "sid": "MRK 15:46"}, "He bought a linen cloth, and taking him down, wound him in the linen cloth, and laid him in a tomb which had been cut out\nof a rock. He rolled a stone against the door of the tomb. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "47", "sid": "MRK 15:47"}, "Maryam Magdalene and Maryam, the mother of Joses, saw where he was laid.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "MRK 16:1"}, "When the Sabbath was past, Maryam Magdalene, and Maryam the mother of Yaqub, and Salome, bought spices, that they might\ncome and anoint him. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "MRK 16:2"}, "Very early on the first day of the week, they came to the tomb when the sun had risen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "MRK 16:3"}, "They were saying amongst themselves, \u201cWho will roll away the stone from the door of the tomb for us?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "MRK 16:4"}, "for it was very big. Looking up, they saw that the stone was rolled back.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "MRK 16:5"}, "Entering into the tomb, they saw a young man sitting on the right side, dressed in a white robe, and they were amazed.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "MRK 16:6"}, "He said to them, \u201cDon\u2019t be amazed. You seek Isa, the Nazarene, who has been crucified. He has risen. He is not here.\nBehold, the place where they laid him! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "MRK 16:7"}, "But go, tell his disciples and Peter, \u2018He goes before you into Galilee. There you will see him, as he said to you.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "MRK 16:8"}, "They went out,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:8 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["TR adds \u201cquickly\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " and fled from the tomb, for trembling and astonishment had come on\nthem. They said nothing to anyone; for they were afraid.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:8\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["One isolated manuscript omits verses 9-20 but adds this \u201cshort ending of Marqus\u201d to the end of verse 8:\n"]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "fqa", "content": ["They told all that had been commanded them briefly to those around Peter. After that, Isa himself sent them out, from east\nto west, with the sacred and imperishable proclamation of eternal\nsalvation."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "MRK 16:9"}, {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU includes the text of verses 9-20, but mentions in a footnote that a few manuscripts omitted it. The\ntranslators of the World English Bible regard Marqus 16:9-20 as reliable based on an overwhelming majority of textual evidence,\nincluding not only the authoritative Greek Majority Text New Testament, but also the TR and many of the manuscripts cited in\nthe NU text."]}], "caller": "+"}, "Now when he had risen early on the first day of the week, he appeared first to Maryam Magdalene, from whom he\nhad cast out seven demons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "MRK 16:10"}, "She went and told those who had been with him, as they mourned and wept.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "MRK 16:11"}, "When they heard that he was alive, and had been seen by her, they disbelieved.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "MRK 16:12"}, "After these things he was revealed in another form to two of them, as they walked, on their way into the country.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "MRK 16:13"}, "They went away and told it to the rest. They didn\u2019t believe them, either.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "MRK 16:14"}, "Afterward he was revealed to the eleven themselves as they sat at the table, and he rebuked them for their unbelief and\nhardness of heart, because they didn\u2019t believe those who had seen him after he had risen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "MRK 16:15"}, "He said to them, ", {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["\u201cGo into all the world, and preach the Good News to the whole creation.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "MRK 16:16"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["He who believes and is baptised will be saved; but he who disbelieves will be condemned.\n"]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "MRK 16:17"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["These signs will accompany those who believe: in my name they will cast out demons; they will speak with new\nlanguages; "]}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "MRK 16:18"}, {"type": "char", "marker": "wj", "content": ["they will take up serpents; and if they drink any deadly thing, it will in no way hurt them; they will lay hands on\nthe sick, and they will recover.\u201d"]}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "MRK 16:19"}, "So then the Lord,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["16:19 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["NU adds \u201cIsa\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, " after he had spoken to them, was received up into heaven, and sat\ndown at the right hand of Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "MRK 16:20"}, "They went out, and preached everywhere, the Lord working with them, and confirming the word by the signs that followed.\nAmen. "]}]}